var tipuesearch={"pages": [{"title":"Command Line Options","text":"Doctran can be supplied with the command-line options shown below.","tags":"","category":"","url":globals.prefix+"command-line.html"},{"title":"Descriptive Comments","text":"A description can be placed anywhere within a block to describe that block's purpose. In the case of declarations of variables-like objects, a description must be placed on the line directly beneath the declaration line. A variable-like object refers to variables, arguments and components. A description made up of two parts, a basic and a detail part.","tags":"","category":"","url":globals.prefix+"description-comments.html"},{"title":"Getting Started","text":"Once you have downloaded and run the installation package on you system, it is best to test that the installation has been successful. To do this use the following steps:\n  - Open up a Doctran Command Prompt, on Windows systems, or a terminal, on other systems.\n  - Type cd testing to move into the testing folder\n  - Then on Windows systems type run_tests.bat or sh run_tests.sh on other systems.","tags":"","category":"","url":globals.prefix+"getting-started.html"},{"title":"Welcome to Doctran 1.2.1","text":" Doctran is a documentation generator for generating API documentation in HTML format from modern Fortran source code. It has full support for Fortran 95 standard and the object oriented parts of the Fortran 2003 standard.","tags":"","category":"","url":globals.prefix+"index.html"},{"title":"Information Comments","text":"An information element specifies a specific property of a block. Any line of the form !> TYPE : DESCRIPTION, where TYPE is a string of alpha numeric characters, will be interpreted by Doctran as a information element. The TYPE specification is not case sensitive.","tags":"","category":"","url":globals.prefix+"information-comments.html"},{"title":"Installation Instructions","text":"Doctran may be run on Windows systems from XP SP3 onwards, and on Linux and Mac OS X systems that support the Mono 2.8 framework or above.","tags":"","category":"","url":globals.prefix+"installation.html"},{"title":"Project Files","text":"The project file is simply a plain text file that contains information about your project. You can specify a project file using the --project_info option","tags":"","category":"","url":globals.prefix+"project-files.html"},{"title":"Author","text":"An author information element is used to specify the author who wrote that block of code. It may be placed within any block of code and the information will be shown on that block's documentation page. The unique author names within all blocks are collect and also shown on the project's index page.","tags":"","category":"","url":globals.prefix+"information-comments/author.html"},{"title":"Linux and Mac OS X Installations","text":"Installation on Unix based systems are distributed as a makeself package. To install place DoctranTrial.sh in the directory you would like to install Doctran within. Then, open a terminal within that directory and run ","tags":"","category":"","url":globals.prefix+"installation/unix.html"},{"title":"Windows Systems","text":"The Windows package comes as a self-installing executable, making installation straightforward. Proceed by following the dialogues. You will be asked to download and install any missing prerequisites, and to add a shortcut to Doctran's command prompt. This is recommended, as loading the command prompt using one of these shortcuts is probably the quickest way of getting started using Doctran.","tags":"","category":"","url":globals.prefix+"installation/windows.html"},{"title":"Author","text":"Use this to specify any additional authors not specified within author information comments within the source.  This can be specified multiple times and take the following form:","tags":"","category":"","url":globals.prefix+"project-files/author.html"},{"title":"Markup","text":"The type of markup used for detailed descriptions. This should be specified only once and take the following form:","tags":"","category":"","url":globals.prefix+"project-files/markup.html"},{"title":"Name","text":"The name of the project to be display within the header and title. This should be specified only once and take the following form:","tags":"","category":"","url":globals.prefix+"project-files/name.html"},{"title":"Searchable","text":"The type of code block that should be indexed and viewable within the documentation search results. This should be specified only once and take the following form:","tags":"","category":"","url":globals.prefix+"project-files/searchable.html"},{"title":"ShowSource","text":"The type of code block that syntax highlighted source code should be included on its page. This should be specified only once and take the following form:","tags":"","category":"","url":globals.prefix+"project-files/showsource.html"}]};